# Build Bible V2 — Chapter 8 (Enterprise SEO)

Spec: `docs/10_BUILD_BIBLE_V2_CHAPTER_08_SEO.md`

## Rules

- Only `public_website` routes may be indexed (`classifyRoute` / `isIndexablePublicRoute`).
- Dashboard, portal, settings, API, auth, and internal routes stay `noindex` (metadata + robots + X-Robots-Tag).
- Public pages use `createPageMetadataForPath` / `PAGE_SEO` — unique titles and descriptions.
- Sitemap contains only validated public canonical URLs on www.
- Structured data must match visible content; never invent reviews or certifications.
- Prefer `/docs/*` public links over `/api/*` in marketing and AI crawler surfaces.
- Never weaken auth, RBAC, RLS, or Paddle billing behaviour.

## This chapter

- Do not commit, push, or deploy from Chapter 8 work.
